 Example n;i
 Init '.'
‚çù Produce and consume `n` messages
‚çù

‚çù Set up the consumer first
 config‚Üê0 2‚ç¥‚ç¨
 config‚ç™‚Üê'bootstrap.servers' 'localhost:9092'
 config‚ç™‚Üê'client.id' 'bhcgrs3550'
 config‚ç™‚Üê'group.id' 'dyalog'

 topic_list‚Üê'animals' 'cars' 'plants'
 consumer‚Üê‚éïNEW Consumer(config topic_list)
 ‚éïDL 5
‚çù Now set up the producer
 config‚Üê0 2‚ç¥‚ç¨
 config‚ç™‚Üê'bootstrap.servers' 'localhost:9092'
 config‚ç™‚Üê'client.id' 'bhc'
 ‚çùconfig‚ç™‚Üê'auto.offset.reset' 'smallest'

 producer‚Üê‚éïNEW Producer config

‚çù Produce onto the animals topic
 :For i :In ‚ç≥n
     producer.produce_record ‚éïNEW #.Record('animals'(75‚Üë'Payload',‚çïi)('key',‚çï4|i))
     :If 0=10|i
         producer.update_outstanding
     :EndIf
 :EndFor

‚çù Produce a few messages to the other topics, too
 producer.produce_record ‚éïNEW #.Record('cars' 'ferrari' 'sportcars')
 producer.produce_record ‚éïNEW #.Record('plants' 'iris' 'flowers')
 producer.update_outstanding

‚çù Let's drain the topics
 :While 0=‚äÉcr‚Üêconsumer.consume_record
     (2‚äÉcr).(Topic Payload Key Partition Offset)
 :EndWhile

‚çù Tidy up
‚çù‚éïEX'producer'
‚çù‚éïEX'consumer'
